Introduction

U-KISS (an acronym for Ubiquitous Korean International Idol Super Star) is a South Korean boy group formed by NH Media in 2008. The group officially debuted in South Korea on August 28th, 2008, with the live performance of their debut song, "Not Young," on Mnet. U-KISS is currently composed of three members: Soohyun, Hoon, and Jun Young.

On January 24, 2022, the three remaining members of U-KISS signed with Tango Music.

In June 2023, former members Eli, Alexander, and AJ teamed up with the group once again to release the album "PLAY LIST," in celebration of U-KISS' 15th debut anniversary.

As of December 31, 2024, U-Kiss's contracts with their company, Tango Music have expired. They have announced that they will be entering an indefinite hiatus. During this notice member Soohyun announced his plans to return as a solo artist in 2025.
